            "content": "## 1. Schema & migration\n\n- [ ] 1.1 Add `pin_item_type` pgEnum (`['chat','project']`) and a `pins` table (`apps/api/src/db/schema/pins.ts`): `user_id` text ŌåÆ `users.id` ON DELETE CASCADE, `item_type` enum, `item_id` uuid, `pinned_at` timestamptz NOT NULL default now(), PK `(user_id,item_type,item_id)`, index `pins_user_pinned_idx` on `(user_id, pinned_at DESC)`; export `Pin` type; register in `schema/index.ts`.\n- [ ] 1.2 Define RLS policies on `pins`: `SELECT`/`DELETE` USING `user_id = current_setting('app.current_user_id', true)`; `INSERT` WITH CHECK adding the per-type accessibility subquery (chatŌåÆchats, projectŌåÆprojects owner check) per design D3; `.enableRLS()`.\n- [ ] 1.3 Remove `pinnedAt` and the `chats_owner_pinned_updated_idx` index from `apps/api/src/db/schema/chats.ts` (keep `chats_owner_updated_idx`).\n- [ ] 1.4 `pnpm --filter api db:generate`; hand-append `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` for `pins` to the generated migration SQL; `drizzle-kit check` passes.\n- [ ] 1.5 Document the new hand-authored migration exception (FORCE append) in `apps/api/CLAUDE.md` Gotchas list.\n\n## 2. API ŌĆö pins feature module\n\n- [ ] 2.1 Create `apps/api/src/pins/` module (`pins.module.ts`, register in `app.module.ts`).\n- [ ] 2.2 `PinsRepository`: `list(userId)` (ordered `pinned_at DESC`), `pin(userId,type,id)` (upsert `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`), `unpin(userId,type,id)`, and a `hydrate` step batch-loading chat titles + project names by id under RLS, dropping non-hydratable rows (design D4).\n- [ ] 2.3 `PinsService` wrapping the repository inside `TenantDbService.runAs`.\n- [ ] 2.4 DTOs + response types: `ItemTypeParamDto` (enum-validated `:itemType`, `ParseUUIDPipe` on `:itemId`), `PinnedItemResponse` (`itemType`, `itemId`, `pinnedAt`, `title`), list response; `@nestjs/swagger` annotations, nullable fields modeled explicitly.\n- [ ] 2.5 `PinsController`: `GET /api/v1/pins`, `PUT /api/v1/pins/:itemType/:itemId`, `DELETE /api/v1/pins/:itemType/:itemId`; identity from the authenticated session only; idempotent writes return well-typed responses.\n\n## 3. API ŌĆö remove legacy chat pin + viewer-scoped pin state\n\n- [ ] 3.1 Remove the `pinned` field from the chat update DTO and drop the pin branch in `chats-repository.ts` `update` (lines ~254-264) and any `pinnedAt` ordering in `findByOwner`.\n- [ ] 3.2 Add a viewer-scoped `pinnedAt` to the chat list read: `LEFT JOIN pins` on `(user_id=:me, item_type='chat', item_id=chat.id)`; include `pinnedAt` in the chat list response type.\n- [ ] 3.3 Add the same viewer-scoped `pinnedAt` to the projects list read/response (`projects-repository.ts` / projects DTO), joined on `item_type='project'`.\n\n## 4. Web ŌĆö services & hooks\n\n- [ ] 4.1 Add `apps/web/lib/services/pins/` ŌĆö `listPins`, `usePins` (query), `usePinItem`/`useUnpinItem` (mutations ŌåÆ `PUT`/`DELETE /api/v1/pins/:type/:id`), with error toasts; query-key factory + list invalidation.\n- [ ] 4.2 Re-point chat pinning: replace `setChatPinned`/`useSetChatPinned` (`lib/services/chat/management.ts`) usage in `chat-item.tsx` to the pins mutations; keep the chat-list `pinnedAt` grouping (`queries.ts`) unchanged in shape, now fed by the viewer-scoped field.\n- [ ] 4.3 Add `pinnedAt` to the project response type (`lib/services/project/types.ts`) and project query wiring.\n\n## 5. Web ŌĆö rail & lists UI\n\n- [ ] 5.1 Render a \"Pinned\" section in the main rail (`app-sidebar`) from `usePins()` ŌĆö mixed chats+projects, `pinned_at DESC`, icon by type, links to the item; matches `AppShell.dc.html` structure.\n- [ ] 5.2 Make the project row pin action live in `project-list-sidebar/index.tsx` (remove the \"coming soon\" disabled placeholder) and add a \"Pinned\" / \"All projects\" grouping above the rest.\n- [ ] 5.3 Confirm the chat list \"Pinned\" group renders from the re-pointed pin state (no visual regression).\n\n## 6. Tests\n\n- [ ] 6.1 `pins` RLS integration spec: per-user isolation (A cannot see/unpin B's pin), absent-identity/`runAsPublic` returns none, and the write-time accessibility gate denies pinning an inaccessible item.\n- [ ] 6.2 `PinsRepository`/`PinsService` unit specs incl. idempotent pin/unpin and hydrate dropping vanished/inaccessible items.\n- [ ] 6.3 `PinsController` spec: path-keyed pin/unpin, enum + UUID validation on params, typed responses.\n- [ ] 6.4 Web unit tests: rail Pinned section renders mixed items; project pin toggle; chat pin re-pointed to `/pins`; project list Pinned grouping.\n- [ ] 6.5 Run `scripts/rls-test.sh` (schema/RLS touched) and `pnpm --filter api test` + `pnpm --filter web test`; lint/typecheck both apps.\n\n## 7. Docs\n\n- [ ] 7.1 Add a dated `CHANGELOG.md` entry; if pinning is on `ROADMAP.md`, remove it there in the same change.\n",
